Researchers from Texas A&M School of Public Health found that hospitalizations from car crashes dropped 7 per cent in 45 states with texting bans between 2003 and 2010  . 
  Arizona, Texas, Montana, Missouri and Oklahoma are the only five states in the US that do not have texting at the wheel bans . 
  Adults between the ages of 25 and 40 are most likely to get in an accident related to texting and driving . 
 